<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="207" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,150,801]" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with complete solid black stripe. Anterolateral margin with black punctures dorsally. Cicatrices with black punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[1037,1144,185,211]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 19K</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with anterior margin yellow (
<figureCitation box="[329,434,220,246]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 19K</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with dark brown stripes (
<figureCitation box="[912,1013,220,246]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[252,1337,194,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-23@30.[237,1350,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. Dorsal and ventral view. H. excavatus sp. n. A–B; H. flexuosus sp. n. C–D; H. nigrosinuatus sp. n. E–F; H. omegoides sp. n. G–H; H. pentagonalis sp. n. I–J; H. rugulosus sp. n. K–L (Scale = 5mm)." pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 19L</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1210,1350,220,246]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[246,1335,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@21.[231,1356,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Hypoxys rugulosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 12A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore dorsal rim shallowly excavated (
<figureCitation box="[596,703,255,281]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[246,1335,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@21.[231,1356,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Hypoxys rugulosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 12A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup half-moon shaped, inner angle acute, ventral margin with developed median triangular projection; touching dorsal rim; visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[246,1335,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@21.[231,1356,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Hypoxys rugulosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 12A–C</figureCitation>
). Paramere club-like, elongated, laterally bent, margin black; anterior lobe slightly developed and rounded; posterior lobe narrow and truncated; inner face of the stalk with tiny carina ending before bent part (
<figureCitation box="[1287,1424,359,385]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[246,1335,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@21.[231,1356,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Hypoxys rugulosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 12B–C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with dorsolateral tufts of long setae separated by dorsal narrow ridge; posterior face longer than wide, basal half rugulose with a central fold, ventral margin biconvex (
<figureCitation box="[877,1016,428,454]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[246,1335,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@21.[231,1356,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Hypoxys rugulosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 12A–D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with median excavation in “U”; expansions setose, rounded, wide, surpassing level of posterolateral angles in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1274,1379,463,489]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[246,1335,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@21.[231,1356,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Hypoxys rugulosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 12D</figureCitation>
). Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[326,429,497,523]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[246,1335,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@21.[231,1356,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Hypoxys rugulosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Fig. 12E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 with posterior margin slightly sinuous, inner angles acuminated to rounded, reaching base of valvifers 9; an almost distal fold hides posterior margin in ventral view; inner margins dark, divergent on distal 2/3, median excavation cup like. Valvulae 9 exposed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="207" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,150,801]" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,601,627]" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Comments.</emphasis>
This species shows the lateral margins of the posterior face remarkably projected ventrally. Only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,304,636,662]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="omegoides">
<emphasis box="[151,304,636,662]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">H. omegoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the proctiger projected ventrally, but in a completely different way; also other parts of the pygophore separate them (
<figureCitation box="[364,513,671,697]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[246,1335,191,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-20@21.[231,1356,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Hypoxys rugulosus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="20" pageNumber="207">Figs. 12A–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[524,611,671,697]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,201,1505]" captionTargetId="figure-20@17.[151,1436,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Hypoxys omegoides sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="20" pageNumber="207">10A–D</figureCitation>
). Female has the genital plates similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1076,1214,671,697]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="207" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flexuosus">
<emphasis box="[1076,1214,671,697]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="207">H. flexuosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and several species with elliptical median excavation of the valvifers 8, but the fold adjacent to posterior margin can separate them.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1177,740,767]" pageId="20" pageNumber="207" type="etymology">
